definition:
συν-βάλλω
 (Rec. συμ-), [in LXX: 2Ch.25:19 (גָּרָה hith.), Isa.46:6 (זוּל), Jer.43:3 (סוּת hi.), Wis.5:8, al. ;] 
to throw together, hence, 
   (a) of speech (before λόγους, Eur., al.), to discuss, confer (sc. λόγους): with dative of person(s), Luk.11:53, WH, mg., Act.17:18; before πρὸς ἀλλήλους, Act.4:15; 
   (b) to reflect, consider, ponder: ἐν τ. καρδίᾳ, Luk.2:19; 
   (with) to meet with, fall in with: Act.20:14; in hostile sense, εἰς πόλεμον, with dative (εἰς μάχην, Polyb.), Luk.14:31; 
   (d) mid., to contribute (Polyb., al.; cf. MM, xxiv): Act.18:27.†
 (AS)
